    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Dissipance, or dissipation factor for sound power, is the ratio of dissipated sound power to incident sound power. The dissipation factor (DF) is a measure of loss-rate of energy of a mode of oscillation (mechanical, electrical, or electromechanical) in a dissipative system. It is the reciprocal of quality factor, which represents the quality of oscillation.",
